                <div class="bg-white p-6 md:p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
                    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-4">LD50 Calculator & Safety Info</h1>
                    
                    <!-- Disclaimer -->
                    <div class="bg-red-100 border-l-4 border-red-600 text-red-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6" role="alert">
                        <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">CRITICAL SAFETY WARNING</p>
                        <p>This calculator is for informational and educational purposes ONLY. It provides a theoretical dose calculation and is **NOT a substitute for professional veterinary advice.**</p>
                        <p class="mt-2 font-semibold">If you suspect your pet has ingested ANY poison, contact your veterinarian or the <a href="https://www.aspca.org/pet-care/animal-poison-control" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline hover:text-red-900">ASPCA Animal Poison Control Center</a> (888-426-4435) immediately.</p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Calculator -->
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-4">Theoretical LD50 Calculator</h2>
                        <p class="mb-4">This tool estimates the number of bait blocks an animal would need to consume to reach the LD50 (Lethal Dose, 50%) based on the product's active ingredient (AI) and the animal's body weight. The LD50 is the dose required to kill half the members of a tested population.</p>
                        <!-- UPDATED NOTE -->
                        <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Note:</strong> This calculator is hard-coded for a specific product example: a <strong>1 oz (28.35g) bait block</strong> containing <strong>0.005% active ingredient (approx 1.42mg)</strong>. The LD50 ratio is assumed at 1.47mg/kg.</p>
                        
                        <div class="space-y-4">
                            <div>
                                <label for="animal-weight" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">1. Animal's Weight (in lbs)</label>
                                <!-- UPDATED INPUT FIELD -->
                                <input type="text" id="animal-weight" inputmode="decimal" oninput="this.value = this.value.replace(/[^0-9.]/g, '').replace(/(\..*?)\./g, '$1')" class="mt-1 block w-full md:w-1/2 rounded-lg border-gray-300 shadow-sm focus:border-green-500 focus:ring-green-500" placeholder="e.g., 20">
                            </div>
                            
                            <!-- REMOVED AI PER BLOCK INPUT FIELD -->
                            
                            <button id="calculate-ld50" class="px-6 py-2 bg-green-700 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg shadow-md hover:bg-green-800 transition focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-green-500 focus:ring-offset-2">
                                Calculate
                            </button>
                        </div>
                        
                        <!-- Result -->
                        <div id="ld50-result" class="mt-6 hidden">
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Result:</h3>
                            <p class="text-lg p-4 bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg"></p>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                                <strong>Note:</strong> This result represents the number of blocks the animal would need to consume *directly* to reach the theoretical LD50, based on your inputs and the 1.47 mg/kg ratio. This is not a toxicity guarantee.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- ADDED LABELS & SDS CONTENT -->
                    <hr class="my-8 border-gray-200">
                    <div class="mt-8">
                        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-6">Product Labels & SDS</h1>
                        <p class="text-lg mb-6">For your convenience and safety, we provide links to the manufacturer's product labels and Safety Data Sheets (SDS) for the materials we may use. Always read the label before any application.</p>
                        
                        <div class="space-y-6">
                            <!-- Section: Rodenticides -->
                            <div>
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">Rodenticides</h2>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
